Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. 

> TIP: Lower heat if salmon begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

While salmon cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @pear{1}.

Add @spinach{5%ounce} and @creamy balsamic dressing{3%ounce} to a large #bowl{}; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Add pear, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @pecans{½%ounce}, @croutons{2}, and @feta cheese{½%cup} to bowl with spinach; toss to combine.

> TIP: Add a drizzle of olive oil if salad seems dry.

Slice salmon crosswise. Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with salmon and serve.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.